715865f-a.title: ??Manhattan: Avenue A - 10th Street (East)
715865f-a.text:
Avenue A, north from East 10th Street, showing this thorough-fare after track removal and repavement by the Works Progress Administration. At the left is the Boys Club, a neighborhood social activity. This structure is detailed in View 2. Wm. Carey, the Commissioner of Sanitation under Mayor La Guardia is the sponsor. He, being individually wealthy, has shown a deep interest in the youth movement. This structure, bearing No's. 161-3 Avenue A, and 285-91 East 10th Street is at the N. W. corner.

May 17, 1937
